      "validated": true,
      "evidence_note": "Repo-wide validation at the pinned commit supports the mpsc category. Production channel use appears concentrated in src/walk.rs via crossbeam_channel. The search pipeline creates a bounded channel, clones Sender handles across parallel walker workers, and sends Batch values containing WorkerResult entries/errors to a receiver path, making MPSC-style result aggregation core to walking/output execution. Receiver cloning is only used for non-batch --exec mode, where multiple job threads consume from the same channel, so competing consumers are present but limited to that feature. No tokio broadcast/watch/mpsc/oneshot, std::sync::mpsc, async_channel, futures mpsc/oneshot, or pub-sub pattern was found outside this crossbeam_channel usage."
